criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Patients aged from 18 to 75 years, with polyps found during surveillance or screening
             colonoscopies.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Contraindications to CV (such as allergy);

          -  Pregnancy or breastfeeding;

          -  Serous cardiopulmonary diseases, severe coagulopathy dysfunction, impaired kidney
             function;

          -  Inability to provide informed consent.
